%N A361189 Infinite sequence of nonzero integers build the greedy way such that the sums Sum_{i = k*2^e..(k+1)*2^e} a(i) with k, e >= 0 are all distinct; each term is minimal in absolute value and in case of a tie, preference is given to the positive value.
%C A361189 This sequence is a variant of A361144 where we allows negative values.
%C A361189 In order for the sequence to be infinite, zero sums are forbidden.
%C A361189 We can arrange the terms of the sequence as the leaves of a perfect infinite binary tree, the sums with e > 0 corresponding to parent nodes; each node will contain a different value and all nonzero values will appear in the tree.
